1
00:00:53,443 --> 00:00:54,803
Hey, will I lose my job then?

2
00:00:55,112 --> 00:00:56,275
What's the doubt in that?

3
00:00:56,849 --> 00:00:59,449
If you hang out with Nedumaran's
daughter, isn't your job at risk?

4
00:01:00,269 --> 00:01:02,152
You should have thought
about it when I called you.

5
00:01:02,354 --> 00:01:03,434
What's this, Kumudha?

6
00:01:03,560 --> 00:01:05,173
Is it really a trap as I said?

7
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:07,163
Nothing like that.

8
00:01:07,985 --> 00:01:09,745
I've already told him
that I had forgotten my phone

9
00:01:09,830 --> 00:01:12,043
at the resort
and that you brought it over.

10
00:01:13,657 --> 00:01:15,937
So, there won't be any
problem after this, right?

11
00:01:16,203 --> 00:01:19,123
No, there won't be.
I've already spoken to my dad.

12
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:23,803
But, when you call Mr. Nedumaran
as dad, it feels weird.

13
00:01:24,203 --> 00:01:25,483
Even I feel the same.

14
00:01:25,782 --> 00:01:28,123
Do you know that I sometimes
call him chef at home?

15
00:01:29,163 --> 00:01:30,403
Oh, no!
- What?

16
00:01:31,508 --> 00:01:34,791
Nothing. By the way,
what's the matter with your sister?

17
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:37,123
What's going on between
your father and sister?

18
00:01:38,803 --> 00:01:41,283
My sister cooks better than me.
- Oh!

19
00:01:41,490 --> 00:01:42,402
But..

20
00:01:43,687 --> 00:01:45,214
She wants to travel the world.

21
00:01:45,910 --> 00:01:47,723
She wants to meet a lot of people.

22
00:01:47,910 --> 00:01:50,923
She wants to connect with them
and hear their stories.

23
00:01:51,563 --> 00:01:54,883
She wants to write it as a book.
That is her wish.

24
00:01:55,970 --> 00:01:59,243
But, our dad forced her
to become a master chef.

25
00:02:00,643 --> 00:02:02,603
So, she ran away from home.

26
00:02:03,963 --> 00:02:05,283
Oh, no!

27
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:07,563
I am the one
you should be feeling bad for.

28
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:11,043
Actually, she escaped.
But, I got stuck with him.

29
00:02:11,670 --> 00:02:15,603
One day, I will also run away.
- Oh, no!

30
00:02:16,083 --> 00:02:18,843
If you run away,
who will fulfil your dad's wish?

31
00:02:19,203 --> 00:02:22,683
Hey, are you supporting me or him?

32
00:02:24,283 --> 00:02:26,403
I will give you an idea.
You cook well, right?

33
00:02:26,510 --> 00:02:28,403
You fulfil his wish.

34
00:02:29,243 --> 00:02:31,243
Oh, no!
Why the unnecessary trouble?

35
00:02:32,194 --> 00:02:33,994
He will find fault even in that.

36
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:41,803
But, I think people from every walk
of life face their own problems.

37
00:02:42,123 --> 00:02:46,320
Debt is my biggest problem.
My family is struggling.

38
00:02:47,683 --> 00:02:49,043
I have to educate my sister.

39
00:02:49,683 --> 00:02:51,923
I have to give her money.

40
00:02:52,603 --> 00:02:53,963
I don't know what she is doing.

41
00:02:55,010 --> 00:02:57,403
I long to provide for my mom.

42
00:02:58,280 --> 00:03:00,003
But, she is working as a house help.

43
00:03:00,603 --> 00:03:04,040
I wanted to do a part-time job
for some extra income.

44
00:03:04,434 --> 00:03:06,951
Because of my mistake,
the shop was taken away.

45
00:03:07,062 --> 00:03:08,182
What are you saying?

46
00:03:08,772 --> 00:03:11,775
Is that the same shop where we ate?
- Yes.

47
00:03:12,930 --> 00:03:14,963
The food there was good.

48
00:03:15,403 --> 00:03:17,283
What can I do? It's my ill fate.

49
00:03:18,963 --> 00:03:20,603
I want to become a chef from here.

50
00:03:20,803 --> 00:03:24,203
But, you are saying that you
don't like the profession I love.

51
00:03:24,460 --> 00:03:25,723
What kind of life is this?

52
00:03:27,207 --> 00:03:28,206
But, I must admit.

53
00:03:28,876 --> 00:03:32,323
I forgot everything
and played the guitar with delight.

54
00:03:32,643 --> 00:03:34,763
I am very happy.
I can't forget it.

55
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:38,843
It's okay. - Let me know
if I have to do it again.

56
00:03:38,923 --> 00:03:40,630
I'll come and play
without charging you.

57
00:03:42,043 --> 00:03:44,403
Even the ones who love
playing wouldn't talk like that.

58
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:48,683
This is my spot.

59
00:03:49,723 --> 00:03:52,123
Okay.
- This is the hostel.

60
00:03:52,310 --> 00:03:53,723
Dogs might chase if you go in.

61
00:03:53,775 --> 00:03:56,148
You go.
- Okay, we'll meet tomorrow.

62
00:03:56,203 --> 00:03:58,683
Okay, bye.
- Bye. - Hey! Your guitar!

63
00:03:59,820 --> 00:04:00,963
Yes.
- Don't you want it?

64
00:04:01,683 --> 00:04:03,603
Here. Wear it.

65
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:08,283
Thank you. I will leave now.
- Ride carefully.

66
00:04:08,331 --> 00:04:09,243
Bye.
- Bye.

67
00:04:42,741 --> 00:04:46,184
Vetri, listen to me patiently.
- Mom.

68
00:04:46,703 --> 00:04:47,787
What is this?

69
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:50,203
How could you let her work?

70
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:51,840
I have told her so many times.

71
00:04:52,106 --> 00:04:56,749
I told her to just study, and that
we'll deal with the problems.

72
00:04:57,214 --> 00:04:58,447
But, she doesn't listen to me.

73
00:04:59,160 --> 00:05:03,043
She told me not to tell you.
What should I do?

74
00:05:03,443 --> 00:05:05,563
Mom, what you are
doing is not right.

75
00:05:07,266 --> 00:05:11,055
Why did you hide it from me?
- Oh, God! Forgive me.

76
00:05:11,585 --> 00:05:14,320
I'm stuck between the two of you.

77
00:05:14,662 --> 00:05:17,403
Okay, what has happened
to her now? How is she?

78
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:21,523
She is in pain.

79
00:05:21,840 --> 00:05:23,243
What led to her disc problem?

80
00:05:23,403 --> 00:05:27,480
They won't allow her
to sit where she works.

81
00:05:27,883 --> 00:05:28,883
Which shop is that?

82
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:34,403
Chitra Clothing Store that is
located on the main road.

83
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:39,000
Oh, God! I've heard that
they treat the employees badly.

84
00:05:39,163 --> 00:05:41,263
You should have told me.
What is this?

85
00:05:41,723 --> 00:05:42,723
Okay, tell me.

86
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:45,843
She's been on her feet
the whole time.

87
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:48,123
Standing continuously

88
00:05:48,963 --> 00:05:52,483
has hurt her spine.
- Her spine?

89
00:05:53,020 --> 00:05:54,140
Yes, Vetri.

90
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:59,440
We should take care of her
from now on.

91
00:05:59,683 --> 00:06:01,923
Where are you now?
- At home.

92
00:06:02,988 --> 00:06:04,588
She didn't tell me anything.

93
00:06:04,760 --> 00:06:09,043
She went to the hospital alone
and then told me all about it.

94
00:06:13,880 --> 00:06:15,883
Vetri..

95
00:06:18,763 --> 00:06:19,843
Hello, Vetri.

96
00:06:20,210 --> 00:06:22,003
Vetri, can you hear me?

97
00:06:22,966 --> 00:06:25,766
Give the phone to Selvi.
- Okay, I'll give it.

98
00:06:27,721 --> 00:06:29,644
Here, your brother is on the line.

99
00:06:30,170 --> 00:06:32,363
Careful, get up slowly.

100
00:06:32,684 --> 00:06:36,487
Sit carefully. Here, talk to him.

101
00:06:37,243 --> 00:06:40,403
Brother.
- Selvi, why?

102
00:06:41,443 --> 00:06:43,803
I wanted to do what I could.

103
00:06:45,403 --> 00:06:48,400
Sorry. I didn't expect this.

104
00:06:48,803 --> 00:06:50,523
I don't know what to say, Selvi.

105
00:06:51,723 --> 00:06:53,723
If you knew,
you wouldn't have let me.

106
00:06:54,083 --> 00:06:55,243
That's why I didn't tell you.

107
00:06:55,803 --> 00:06:57,603
Okay, take rest.

108
00:06:58,323 --> 00:07:00,723
I will talk to you later.
- Shall I give the phone to mom?

109
00:07:00,990 --> 00:07:04,003
No, I will go home
and then call her.

110
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:06,403
I'll hang up.
- Okay.

111
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:15,603
Hey, why are you talking alone?

112
00:07:19,314 --> 00:07:21,216
I asked you to enquire
about the job. Did you?

113
00:07:22,203 --> 00:07:23,883
Don't get me started.

114
00:07:24,486 --> 00:07:25,696
Migration workers have come in.

115
00:07:26,321 --> 00:07:28,001
No openings
for the next two months.

116
00:07:28,991 --> 00:07:30,351
When we ask for more salary,

117
00:07:30,576 --> 00:07:32,816
they work for 10 hours
at half of our salary.

118
00:07:33,483 --> 00:07:37,563
They seem shocked when I asked
for a high salary for only four hours.

119
00:07:38,750 --> 00:07:41,473
We can't do anything.
We have to wait. Okay?

120
00:07:41,890 --> 00:07:45,003
'Vetri, you've to deliver
food to room no 108.'

121
00:07:45,843 --> 00:07:47,283
'Vetri, are you there?'

122
00:07:48,594 --> 00:07:51,837
Hey, Vetri, they are saying
something. Ask them what it is.

123
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:55,003
'Vetri, deliver food to room 108.'

124
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:58,323
Talk to them, or you
might lose this job as well.

125
00:07:59,523 --> 00:08:01,563
Okay, sir, I'll come.
- 'Come soon.'

126
00:08:05,235 --> 00:08:08,075
When are you coming home?

127
00:08:08,947 --> 00:08:11,870
I will feel at peace
if you come there.

128
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:15,643
Do you miss me a lot?

129
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:22,323
I've missed you ever since
you moved out after your wedding.

130
00:08:23,220 --> 00:08:24,163
Okay, Dad.

131
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:30,003
But, I like being here
more than being at home.

132
00:08:30,940 --> 00:08:34,163
Actually, I am happy here, Dad.

133
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:36,443
What are you saying, dear?

134
00:08:37,563 --> 00:08:41,040
Whatever it is,
can I just leave you like that?

135
00:08:42,523 --> 00:08:45,123
You need someone to take
care of you at this time, right?

136
00:08:48,403 --> 00:08:49,723
That's not a problem, Dad.

137
00:08:50,683 --> 00:08:53,243
I grew up here.

138
00:08:54,003 --> 00:08:57,363
I have Aishu to take care of me.
Rajan is here.

139
00:08:58,140 --> 00:09:02,323
Also, I feel
comfortable being here.

140
00:09:06,243 --> 00:09:10,520
Dad, don't worry about anything.
I will be fine, okay?

141
00:09:11,563 --> 00:09:12,963
I am safe here.

142
00:09:15,264 --> 00:09:16,264
Okay, dear.

143
00:09:17,266 --> 00:09:20,386
If you've decided, what can I say?

144
00:09:21,563 --> 00:09:22,963
Okay, dear..

145
00:09:23,605 --> 00:09:24,725
Thank you, Dad.

146
00:09:27,523 --> 00:09:28,883
Riya.
- Tell me, Dad.

147
00:09:28,960 --> 00:09:32,803
If you want anything,
call me immediately, okay?

148
00:09:34,160 --> 00:09:35,443
Bye.
- Bye, Dad.

149
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:44,280
Okay, thank you.

150
00:09:46,900 --> 00:09:50,323
Uncle, what happened?
Is it something important?

151
00:09:50,923 --> 00:09:55,196
You know what is going
on in Riya's life, right? - Yes.

152
00:09:56,380 --> 00:10:00,963
She shouldn't think there's no one
for her, in any situation.

153
00:10:02,163 --> 00:10:04,363
I know your work pressure.

154
00:10:05,403 --> 00:10:08,843
But, I don't know
whom to trust right now, Rajan.

155
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:17,243
So, you please take
care of her in this situation.

156
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:20,382
Take care of her.
- Sure, uncle.

157
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:31,160
What are you
room service people thinking?

158
00:10:32,883 --> 00:10:34,840
Is this a resort?
What are you all thinking?

159
00:10:37,723 --> 00:10:40,083
Yes, come. Stand here..

160
00:10:40,599 --> 00:10:42,639
They are taking advantage
because of you.

161
00:10:43,830 --> 00:10:47,243
Sir, what happened?
- What happened, eh?

162
00:10:47,843 --> 00:10:49,763
Will anything happen here
without your knowledge?

163
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:53,283
What happened?
- I will tell you.

164
00:10:54,123 --> 00:10:55,922
Hey, didn't I tell you
to call the manager?

165
00:10:55,970 --> 00:10:57,393
He said he will come.
- Why are you standing here?

166
00:10:57,441 --> 00:10:58,883
Go and get him.
- I'll go, sir.

167
00:11:00,843 --> 00:11:02,723
Excuse me, sir,
I want to say something.

168
00:11:03,010 --> 00:11:05,083
As you know,
we run this exclusive resort.

169
00:11:05,230 --> 00:11:07,080
We have so many
variety of dishes here.

170
00:11:07,376 --> 00:11:10,016
Then, why do you buy food
from outside and eat it?

171
00:11:10,523 --> 00:11:14,080
Sir, there are a variety of dishes,
I'm not complaining about that.

172
00:11:14,203 --> 00:11:17,083
The starting price here
ranges from Rs. 700-800.

173
00:11:17,261 --> 00:11:19,654
I can eat three full meals
at the same price.

174
00:11:19,721 --> 00:11:22,454
Customers come here
to save on cost.

175
00:11:22,558 --> 00:11:24,681
So, how can you
charge them like this?

176
00:11:24,790 --> 00:11:26,803
Sir, just to make you understand,

177
00:11:27,145 --> 00:11:28,998
what you eat here
is not normal food.

178
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:31,203
It is done with clean
and fresh inventory.

179
00:11:32,203 --> 00:11:36,603
Moreover, it is cooked
by the master, the GOAT,

180
00:11:36,830 --> 00:11:39,640
Chef, Mr. Nedumaran.
- Yes, I know, sir.

181
00:11:39,730 --> 00:11:43,323
I am also a fan of Mr. Nedumaran.
- Of course, who else is not?

182
00:11:43,950 --> 00:11:48,603
At this resort, large crowds gather
to enjoy Chef Nedumaran's food.

183
00:11:48,834 --> 00:11:52,071
But, I'm not satisfied.
How can you charge so much, sir?

184
00:11:52,248 --> 00:11:54,108
Good food equals fair price.

185
00:11:54,570 --> 00:11:57,683
LHS equals RHS.
You understand, I believe.

186
00:11:58,051 --> 00:12:00,864
Sir, delivery guys are not
allowed inside the resort.

187
00:12:01,046 --> 00:12:05,009
That's why I asked the room boy
to get the parcel, sir.

188
00:12:05,163 --> 00:12:06,523
Sir, it is not fair.

189
00:12:06,650 --> 00:12:08,312
What you are saying
is not right, sir.

190
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:10,267
You keep asking me questions.

191
00:12:10,350 --> 00:12:14,203
If you keep talking like this,
I'll have to escalate the issue.

192
00:12:14,350 --> 00:12:17,763
Sir, what I eat and where
I eat is my personal choice.

193
00:12:17,830 --> 00:12:18,963
Don't interfere in that.

194
00:12:19,070 --> 00:12:21,123
Just you may go now.
- Sir, you are an educated person.

195
00:12:21,210 --> 00:12:23,643
Why are you talking like this?
I don't.. - Excuse me, sir.

196
00:12:23,890 --> 00:12:24,963
I will deal with this.

197
00:12:26,323 --> 00:12:27,283
What happened?

198
00:12:28,081 --> 00:12:29,323
Sir, that is..

199
00:12:30,417 --> 00:12:32,860
I got the parcel and handed it
over to the guest as requested.

200
00:12:33,130 --> 00:12:35,683
That's why he is shouting, sir.
- Am I shouting?

201
00:12:36,381 --> 00:12:39,701
Hey, do I look like a fool to you?
- John, look here.

202
00:12:40,587 --> 00:12:43,162
There is no rule that says you
cannot order food from outside.

203
00:12:44,040 --> 00:12:45,403
Why are you stressing the guest?

204
00:12:47,203 --> 00:12:50,603
If the guest orders food from
outside, why do you deliver it?

205
00:12:50,883 --> 00:12:52,083
That's not in the rules.

206
00:12:52,923 --> 00:12:55,720
If you're here, who will look after
the other guests? Go back to work.

207
00:12:55,950 --> 00:12:57,523
I will go, sir. Go.

208
00:12:58,090 --> 00:13:00,243
Sir, next time, there won't be
any issue. - It's okay.

209
00:13:00,310 --> 00:13:02,170
Okay, thank you, sir.
- Thank you so much. - Thank you.

210
00:13:04,230 --> 00:13:06,640
Mr. Rajan, what are you doing?

211
00:13:07,083 --> 00:13:10,963
If you behave like this with
the guest, our revenue will drop.

212
00:13:12,443 --> 00:13:14,403
John, don't mind
that I'm being harsh.

213
00:13:14,669 --> 00:13:16,338
But, there is no point
in talking to you.

214
00:13:16,883 --> 00:13:18,763
Whatever I say,
you won't understand.

215
00:13:19,123 --> 00:13:21,360
Your point of view
is only about the kitchen.

216
00:13:21,763 --> 00:13:22,843
But, it's not the same for me.

217
00:13:23,643 --> 00:13:25,643
I have to see
all the aspects of this resort.

218
00:13:27,003 --> 00:13:27,963
Leave it.

219
00:13:28,790 --> 00:13:29,843
Continue with your work.

220
00:13:35,043 --> 00:13:36,403
I don't understand?

221
00:13:47,369 --> 00:13:48,229
Okay, sir.

222
00:13:53,330 --> 00:13:54,643
Who is it?
Uthaman?

223
00:13:55,210 --> 00:13:57,789
That was a creditor.
- Oh..

224
00:14:02,134 --> 00:14:03,934
I don't know what to do, Pandi.
- Why?

225
00:14:04,563 --> 00:14:05,923
Ms. Bhavani's shop also is closed.

226
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:08,283
I don't know what she is doing.

227
00:14:08,843 --> 00:14:11,803
Not only that, I can't do anything
without my monthly salary.

228
00:14:12,283 --> 00:14:13,923
My head is spinning.

229
00:14:14,771 --> 00:14:16,411
We will figure something out.

230
00:14:17,803 --> 00:14:20,363
I can't stop thinking
about what that guy said.

231
00:14:21,523 --> 00:14:24,120
Yes, he spoke too much.
- Yes.

232
00:14:24,403 --> 00:14:27,643
I am so angry
that I want to build a resort.

233
00:14:28,283 --> 00:14:30,043
Can we build one?
- Yes.

234
00:14:30,280 --> 00:14:33,360
Only if I set it up and provide
John with a room service uniform,

235
00:14:33,643 --> 00:14:35,043
will I die peacefully.

236
00:14:35,374 --> 00:14:38,504
Hey! Why are you talking
about dying now?

237
00:14:39,296 --> 00:14:43,013
This problem led me to a fantastic
business idea. Shall I tell you?

238
00:14:43,680 --> 00:14:46,200
If you tell me to open a tea
shop outside this resort,

239
00:14:46,323 --> 00:14:47,840
I will kill you.
- Not that.

240
00:14:48,263 --> 00:14:51,463
We could get food from outside
and give it to the guests.

241
00:14:51,683 --> 00:14:53,443
What if we take
a commission from them?

242
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:55,643
That is wrong.

243
00:14:55,923 --> 00:14:59,483
They eat outside
because the food here is expensive.

244
00:14:59,983 --> 00:15:01,603
How can you do this?

245
00:15:02,194 --> 00:15:04,637
Hey! You made me
a villain in a second.

246
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:06,403
I have an idea.

247
00:15:06,490 --> 00:15:10,170
Why don't we put a small
kitchen set inside the resort

248
00:15:10,323 --> 00:15:13,043
and provide food
for the guests at a lower cost?

249
00:15:13,883 --> 00:15:15,363
People here are like hounds.

250
00:15:15,749 --> 00:15:18,229
If they find out,
they'll tear you to pieces.

251
00:15:18,460 --> 00:15:20,963
The shop will do well
if it's in the right spot.

252
00:15:21,547 --> 00:15:22,833
I don't want to do this.

253
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:24,723
They have already kicked me
out of the kitchen.

254
00:15:24,820 --> 00:15:26,923
Are you planning to kick me
out of the resort?

255
00:15:27,020 --> 00:15:30,043
Okay, leave it.
This seems risky.

256
00:15:30,681 --> 00:15:32,281
But..
- But?

257
00:15:32,720 --> 00:15:34,603
We have to do something about John.

258
00:15:35,310 --> 00:15:36,913
Why are you talking like me?

259
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:39,106
Okay, leave it. Don't feel bad.

260
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:41,843
Let's keep a doll.
- A doll? What doll?

261
00:15:42,563 --> 00:15:43,883
The doll.

262
00:15:44,120 --> 00:15:46,523
If we twist its hands and legs..

263
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:49,483
I am more scared of you
than the doll.

264
00:15:50,163 --> 00:15:51,600
Do it soon.
- Lift it.

265
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:53,643
Lift it well..

266
00:15:59,376 --> 00:16:02,453
Are you alright, Riya?
Shall I get you a pill?

267
00:16:02,560 --> 00:16:06,480
No, I don't want that.
I will be fine if I get some sleep.

268
00:16:07,493 --> 00:16:10,136
Then take rest.
I will leave. Bye.

269
00:16:11,290 --> 00:16:12,323
Rajan.

270
00:16:13,670 --> 00:16:16,403
I have some doubts
about our resort.

271
00:16:21,883 --> 00:16:24,883
Why is the food
in our resort so expensive?

272
00:16:25,480 --> 00:16:28,643
If we reduce the cost,
we can run it better, right?

273
00:16:28,910 --> 00:16:30,883
You asked such
a big question so easily.

274
00:16:31,480 --> 00:16:33,043
Tell me, I will learn.

275
00:16:33,723 --> 00:16:35,403
What you asked
is not just a question.

276
00:16:36,083 --> 00:16:37,083
It's history.

277
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:39,843
I hate history.

278
00:16:41,160 --> 00:16:43,723
Even I don't like it.
But, I have to know.

279
00:16:44,243 --> 00:16:46,763
I've had this doubt
for a long time.

280
00:16:46,890 --> 00:16:50,323
There were so many negative
feedback and comments.

281
00:16:50,610 --> 00:16:52,763
Why didn't anyone think about it?

282
00:16:54,765 --> 00:16:56,965
We can't go against
Mr. Nedumaran's rules.

283
00:16:57,603 --> 00:17:01,956
It's already decided
what to do and what not to do.

284
00:17:05,843 --> 00:17:07,520
Since you are the one
after your dad,

285
00:17:07,883 --> 00:17:10,163
he had asked me
to explain it to you.

286
00:17:10,803 --> 00:17:12,563
Thank God,
you asked at the right time.

287
00:17:13,130 --> 00:17:14,163
Let me explain.

288
00:17:29,360 --> 00:17:30,483
Rule number one.

289
00:17:31,530 --> 00:17:32,923
Discipline and behaviour.

290
00:18:20,360 --> 00:18:23,803
Sir, this is newly built.
- Oh, lovely.

291
00:18:25,203 --> 00:18:28,123
Was it there when you visited?
- No, it was not.

292
00:18:28,220 --> 00:18:29,443
There was nothing.

293
00:18:30,240 --> 00:18:32,776
What's your name?
- My name is Vetri.

294
00:18:34,320 --> 00:18:37,643
Vetri, do one thing.
Bring Nedumaran.

295
00:18:37,760 --> 00:18:38,843
Mr. Nedumaran?

296
00:18:39,411 --> 00:18:41,851
Sir, you can't meet him
as easily as you think.

297
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:44,443
Do you think
I am a fan of Nedumaran?

298
00:18:45,163 --> 00:18:48,883
It's not like that. He is my
old friend. Go and get him.

299
00:18:49,080 --> 00:18:52,163
Sir, you have got
the wrong person for that.

300
00:18:52,643 --> 00:18:54,843
What did you say?
- Nothing, sir.

301
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:57,883
Tell him that Leo is here.
He will definitely come.

302
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,643
Okay, sir.
- This is the room, right?

303
00:19:00,803 --> 00:19:03,523
I will go. You go and get him.

304
00:19:04,160 --> 00:19:07,280
Is Chika here?
Chef Chika.

305
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:09,723
Call him too.
- Chika?

306
00:19:10,140 --> 00:19:11,723
There is no chef
with that name.

307
00:19:13,043 --> 00:19:13,923
Is that so?

308
00:19:16,640 --> 00:19:19,320
Okay, go and call Nedumaran.
- Okay, sir.

309
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:22,163
I keep landing in trouble.

310
00:19:24,643 --> 00:19:27,043
Hold on for a minute,
get the pepper. - Yes, Chef.

311
00:19:28,323 --> 00:19:30,363
Do you want me to pour it on top?
- Yes.

312
00:19:30,810 --> 00:19:32,163
Okay.
- That's fine.

313
00:19:37,003 --> 00:19:38,283
Here you go, Chef.
- Yeah.

314
00:19:43,163 --> 00:19:44,403
That should be fine, John.

315
00:19:44,643 --> 00:19:46,763
Just take this and..
- I will just come, Chef.

316
00:19:48,403 --> 00:19:49,763
Where is the order list?

317
00:19:49,963 --> 00:19:51,203
It's not a food list, sir.

318
00:19:51,883 --> 00:19:55,803
There is a guy named Leo.
Says he is Mr. Nedumaran's friend.

319
00:19:57,603 --> 00:19:59,560
He is waiting in his room
to meet him.

320
00:19:59,992 --> 00:20:03,995
Anybody can claim that they know
him. Can he meet all of them?

321
00:20:04,330 --> 00:20:06,923
You..
- John. - Chef.

322
00:20:07,875 --> 00:20:09,075
I am coming, Chef.

323
00:20:10,323 --> 00:20:11,963
Tell him
I will come after plating this.

324
00:20:13,483 --> 00:20:14,643
Plating..
- Yes.. I will tell him.

325
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:18,603
Did you hear that? He will
come after plating it. You go.

326
00:20:18,824 --> 00:20:20,160
Okay.
Sir..

327
00:20:20,563 --> 00:20:24,043
Is there anyone named
Chef Chika in the kitchen?

328
00:20:26,280 --> 00:20:28,843
I mean.. He was asking.

329
00:20:29,363 --> 00:20:31,123
Chika?
- Yes.

330
00:20:33,732 --> 00:20:36,486
There is no..
- Room number? - Sir.

331
00:20:40,763 --> 00:20:43,192
Room number?
- He is asking you the room number.

332
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:44,923
Sir, room number 211.

333
00:20:51,403 --> 00:20:52,443
Thank you, sir.

334
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:07,803
Hey, Nedumaran!
- Leo!

335
00:21:08,210 --> 00:21:10,123
Yes.
- How are you?

336
00:21:10,243 --> 00:21:13,003
I am doing great.
How are you?

337
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:15,643
I am fine as usual.
- Wonderful.

338
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:18,083
It's been a long time.
- Yes.

339
00:21:18,710 --> 00:21:20,483
Where did Chika go?

340
00:21:22,510 --> 00:21:23,483
Chika?

341
00:21:24,083 --> 00:21:25,483
I don't know who he is.

342
00:21:26,003 --> 00:21:29,163
Chika, Nedumaran. You both
were friends. Did you forget?

343
00:21:29,643 --> 00:21:30,683
Hey.

344
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:33,963
I don't remember anyone like that.
Then how would I forget?

345
00:21:34,878 --> 00:21:36,681
You really don't remember Chika?

346
00:21:36,750 --> 00:21:38,443
Hey, I don't know.

347
00:21:38,690 --> 00:21:40,163
Chidambaram, Nedumaran.

348
00:21:40,930 --> 00:21:41,843
Did you forget?

349
00:21:47,283 --> 00:21:49,963
There are many people around.
You know, I'm in the hotel industry.

350
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:53,083
I can't remember everyone.
Moreover, I am getting old.

351
00:21:54,287 --> 00:21:56,050
Good that you didn't forget me.

352
00:21:56,108 --> 00:21:58,071
How can I forget you,
useless fellow?

353
00:22:00,203 --> 00:22:01,003
Come in.

354
00:22:01,720 --> 00:22:03,843
The TV remote is not working.
That's why I asked you to come.

355
00:22:04,210 --> 00:22:05,363
Check it.
- Okay, sir.

356
00:22:19,720 --> 00:22:22,163
I had to leave the kitchen
midway because you called.

357
00:22:22,520 --> 00:22:25,283
I will go back, okay?
- Okay, Nedumaran, carry on.

358
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:29,676
Sir, it's working now.
- Thank you.
